{{nihongo|'''''Super Smash Bros. Brawl'''''|<U+5927><U+4E71><U+95D8><U+30B9><U+30DE><U+30C3><U+30B7><U+30E5><U+30D6><U+30E9><U+30B6><U+30FC><U+30BA>X|Dairant<U+014D> Sumasshu Buraz<U+0101>zu Ekkusu|Great Fray Smash Brothers X}}, frequently abbreviated as ''SSBB'', is a [[versus fighting game|fighting game]] for [[Nintendo]]'s forthcoming [[video game console|console]] [[Wii]]. Its official trailer was first unveiled at [[E3]] [[2006]]. As the third iteration in the massively successful series, it has been confirmed that it will support some [[computer network|network]] features and [[Internet]] play ([[Wi-Fi]]).<ref name="E3 2005">{{cite web|last=Casamassina |first=Matt |authorlink=Matt Casamassina |coauthors= | date=[[2005-05-17]] |url=http://wii.ign.com/articles/670/670552p1.html |title=E<U+00B3> 2005: ''Smash Bros.'' For Revolution |format= |work= |pages= |publisher=[[IGN]] | language= |accessdate=2006-05-03 |accessyear= }}</ref><ref name="E3 2006">{{cite web|last=Casamassina |first=Matt |authorlink=Matt Casamassina |coauthors=Peer Schneider | date=[[2006-05-10]] |url=http://wii.ign.com/articles/707/707504p1.html |title=E<U+00B3> 2006: Super Smash Bros. Brawl  |format= |work= |pages= |publisher=[[IGN]] | language= |accessdate=2006-08-01 |accessyear= }}</ref> ''Brawl'' is the first ''[[Super Smash Bros. series|Super Smash Bros.]]'' game that features a character from a franchise not owned by [[Nintendo]] with the inclusion of [[Solid Snake]] from [[Konami]]'s ''[[Metal Gear (series)|Metal Gear]]'' series. Although originally suggested to be a launch title, ''Super Smash Bros. Brawl'' is slated for release sometime in 2007. ''Super Smash Bros. Brawl'' is currently the most anticipated game on any system according to [[IGN]]'s Top 100 Games list. <ref name="IGNtop">{{cite web |date=[[2006-08-26]] |url=http://games.ign.com/topgames/|title=Top 100 Games|publisher=[[IGN]] |accessdate=2006-08-26}}</ref>

==Confirmed characters==
