[[Image:Ssbbrawl3.jpg|right|thumb|300px|Left to right: [[Link (Legend of Zelda)|Link]], [[Mario]], [[Samus Aran|Zero Suit Samus]], [[Pikachu]], [[Pit (Kid Icarus)|Pit]], [[Kirby (Nintendo)|Kirby]], and [[Meta Knight]].]]

===Kirby===
{{main|Kirby (Nintendo)}}
{{nihongo|'''Kirby'''|<U+30AB><U+30FC><U+30D3><U+30A3>|K<U+0101>bi}} is the main character of the ''Kirby'' series, first appearing in ''[[Kirby's Dream Land]]'' for the [[Game Boy]]. Kirby has appeared in both ''Super Smash Bros.'' and ''Super Smash Bros. Melee'', having the ability to suck opponents into his mouth, taking on aspects of that character's appearance, and copying one of that character's signature attacks. This ability gives Kirby a wide range of possible moves.  Kirby's "Super Smash" move is his "Cook" power from ''Kirby Super Star'', which involves boiling enemies in a pot.

===Link===
{{main|Link (Legend of Zelda)}}
{{nihongo|'''Link'''|<U+30EA><U+30F3><U+30AF>|Rinku}}, the hero of the [[Legend of Zelda series|''Legend of Zelda'' series]], is a Hylian swordsman who has appeared as a fighter in both previous ''Super Smash Bros.'' games. Link's swordplay, signature downward strike, and bow are briefly featured in the E3 trailer.  Also demonstrated in the trailer is his Super Smash attack, in which he slashes at his opponent while they are trapped between two Triforces (see below). Although the ''[[The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time|Ocarina of Time]]'' incarnation of Link appears in ''Super Smash Bros.'' and again in ''Melee'', the ''[[The Legend of Zelda: Twilight Princess|Twilight Princess]]'' incarnation appears in ''Brawl'', still wielding the [[Master Sword]].

===Mario===
{{main|Mario}}
{{nihongo|'''Mario'''|<U+30DE><U+30EA><U+30AA>}}, an Italian plumber, is the main character of the myriads of games in the ''Super Mario'' series, and is present in both of the ''Super Smash Bros.'' games. Mario's fireball attack, present in both previous games, is seen in the E3 trailer, as well as his new Super Smash move, where he projects a massive blast of fire that moves across the entire stage.

===Meta Knight===
{{main|Meta Knight}}
{{nihongo|'''Meta Knight'''|<U+30E1><U+30BF><U+30CA><U+30A4><U+30C8>|Meta Naito}} is a recurring character from the ''Kirby'' series, and is the second of the series to become a ''Super Smash Bros.'' fighter.  In the trailer shown at E3 2006, he can be seen performing quick sword strikes and blocking an attack with his cloak, which blends into the background. He is also shown jumping multiple times in midair, an ability previously held only by Kirby and [[Jigglypuff]] in past ''Super Smash Bros.'' games.  During the trailer, Meta Knight's wings only appear while he is in midair. The official website confirms that his symbol is the same as Kirby's: the Warp Star.<ref name="meta"> [http://www.smashbros.com/en/characters/index.html Meta Knight bio] ''Smashbros.com''. URL Accessed May 27, 2006.</ref>

===Pikachu===
{{main|Pikachu}}
<!-- If you have a source that says, in English, that Pikachu's "Super Smash" is Raichu, then please cite it. Otherwise, it IS fan speculation. --> 
{{nihongo|'''Pikachu'''|<U+30D4><U+30AB><U+30C1><U+30E5><U+30A6>|Pikach<U+016B>}} is the unofficial mascot of the ''[[Pok<U+00E9>mon]]'' series, and has appeared in both previous ''Super Smash Bros.'' games. While its trademark attacks are seen in the trailer, including Thunder, Thunder Jolt, and Quick Attack, its Super Smash attack has yet to be seen.
 
Pikachu became iconic and most famous in the [[Pok<U+00E9>mon (anime)|''Pok<U+00E9>mon'' anime]]. Its first video game appearances were in [[Pok<U+00E9>mon Red and Blue|''Pok<U+00E9>mon Red'' and ''Blue'']] for the original Game Boy and then as the lead Pok<U+00E9>mon in ''[[Pok<U+00E9>mon Yellow]]'' for the Game Boy Color.  Since then, it has been included in every ''Pok<U+00E9>mon'' video game made to date.

===Pit===
{{main|Pit (Kid Icarus)}}
{{nihongo|'''Pit'''|<U+30D4><U+30C3><U+30C8>|Pitto}}, the hero of ''[[Kid Icarus]]'', makes his first playable appearance since the 1991 [[Game Boy]] game ''[[Kid Icarus: Of Myths and Monsters]]''. He is shown in the trailer fighting again with the Sacred Bow of Palutena, which now has the previously unseen ability to separate into two short blades for close-range combat. In addition, he wears a pair of glowing rings which slide onto the Sacred Bow when he prepares to fire light arrows from it. The rings retract back onto his arm after use. In the trailer video, he is seen jumping multiple times in midair as Meta Knight does. Pit's symbol is a bow and arrow tilted at an angle as shown under his bio on the official website.<ref name="pit"> [http://www.smashbros.com/en/characters/chara2/index.html Pit bio] ''Smashbros.com''. URL Accessed [[May 27]], [[2006]].</ref>

===Samus Aran===
{{main|Samus Aran}}
<!-- 

READ THIS ALL EDITORS: 

PLEASE do not speculate on how Samus will change into Zero Suit Samus. We do not know the specifics of it at this time. It could be like Zelda/Sheik, it could be related to her Super Smash attack, or they could still be separate characters on the menu; we just don't know yet. The wording on the official site is too vague to say for certain, and the trailer is not a gameplay video.
-->
{{nihongo|'''Samus Aran'''|<U+30B5><U+30E0><U+30B9><U+30FB><U+30A2><U+30E9><U+30F3>|Samusu Aran}}, the heroine of the [[Metroid series|''Metroid'']] series, has appeared in both previous ''Super Smash Bros.'' games. She returns in ''Brawl'' not just in her Power Suit, but also as Zero Suit Samus, which is based on her unsuited form from ''[[Metroid: Zero Mission]]''. The official website states that Zero Suit Samus "is not a pure character addition," but rather a special mode for Samus which manifests under "certain conditions," the specifics of which are currently unknown. The trailer confirms that Samus's Arm Cannon returns as her primary attack while Zero Suit Samus is shown wielding a gun that can transform into an energy whip.
<ref name="sam"> [http://www.smashbros.com/en/characters/chara3/index.html Zero Suit Samus bio] ''Smashbros.com''. URL Accessed May 27, 2006.</ref>

===Solid Snake===
[[Image:SSBB_Snake.jpg|[[Solid Snake]] sneaking up on [[Link (Legend of Zelda)|Link]]|200px|right|thumb]]
{{main|Solid Snake}}
{{nihongo|'''Solid Snake'''|<U+30BD><U+30EA><U+30C3><U+30C9><U+30FB><U+30B9><U+30CD><U+30FC><U+30AF>|Soriddo Sun<U+0113>ku}}, the main character from [[Konami]]'s ''[[Metal Gear (series)|Metal Gear]]'' franchise, is the first third-party character to become a ''Super Smash Bros.'' fighter. He appears in ''Brawl'' as he does in ''[[Metal Gear Solid 2|MGS2]]'', though with facial hair reminiscent of [[Big Boss|Naked Snake]] from ''[[Metal Gear Solid 3|MGS3]]''. Snake's moves are not showcased in the trailer, but ''Brawl's'' director, [[Masahiro Sakurai]], states on the official website that since he did not want to incorporate real-world weapons into the game, Snake instead will use a variety of explosives, including rocket launchers (as they might be "humorous" if used in-game), and fight hand-to-hand. Snake will also have use of his trademark cardboard box, which he is seen hiding in near the end of the trailer. 
 
Snake's symbol is that of the FOX organization from ''MGS3''.<ref name="snake">[http://www.smashbros.com/en/characters/chara5/index.html Snake bio] "Smashbros.com". URL Accessed May 30, 2006</ref>

===Wario===
{{main|Wario}}
{{nihongo|'''Wario'''|<U+30EF><U+30EA><U+30AA>}}, Mario's rival and star of the ''[[WarioWare, Inc.]]'' and ''[[Wario Land]]'' games, makes his first playable appearance in the series.  His appearance is based on his ''WarioWare'' costume. In the E3 trailer, one of his attacks is atomic [[flatulence]], called the "Wario Waft" according to his profile on the official website. Wario's gas builds up over time. His symbol is the letter "W".<ref name="wario">[http://www.smashbros.com/en/characters/chara4/index.html Wario bio] ''Smashbros.com''. URL Accessed May 27, 2006.</ref>
